    "explanation": "'He's probably busy': Sarà occupato, immagino. The word 'immagino' (I imagine) confirms this is a guess, and Italian marks a guess about the present with the future: 'sarà occupato' = 'he's probably busy'. The present 'è occupato' would state it flatly; the future of probability keeps it a supposition.",
    "examiner_note": "Suppressed for the same reason as the other probability items.",
    "version": 1
