  {
    "external_id": "fu_prob_ant_01",
    "info_display": "suppress",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "verb_form.future",
    "subtopic": "usage.probability",
    "difficulty": 4,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Completa con una supposizione sul passato: 'Non è ancora arrivato: ____ il treno.' (perdere, azione probabile nel passato)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": true,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 0.5,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.usage.probability",
        "label": "futuro anteriore for a past guess (avrà perso)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "avrà perso",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "ha perso",
          "avrà perduto"
        ]
      },
      {
        "order_index": 1,
        "credit": 0.5,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.formation.future_anteriore",
        "label": "futuro anteriore formation (avrà + participle)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "avrà perso",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "perderà"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "perdere",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "perdere - to lose / to miss",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.perdere.verb.translation"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "lemma": "treno",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "treno - train",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.treno.noun.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'He must have missed the train': Non e ancora arrivato: avra perso il treno. Just as the simple future guesses about the present, the futuro anteriore guesses about the PAST: 'avra perso il treno' means 'he's probably missed the train'. The plain passato prossimo 'ha perso' would state it as known; the compound future carries the supposition about a completed action. Two skills sit here: choosing the future-of-probability for a past guess, and building the futuro anteriore (avra + perso).",
    "examiner_note": "Two markpoints per Rev 27: the probability USAGE and the futuro anteriore FORMATION both fire full on the one correct answer, weighted 0.5 each so item marks stay 1. Suppressed (the probability breadcrumb leaks). 'ha perso' is the wrong-tense catch; 'perderà' is the simple-future miss.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "fu_prob_ant_02",
    "info_display": "suppress",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "verb_form.future",
    "subtopic": "usage.probability",
    "difficulty": 4,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Completa con una supposizione sul passato: 'La luce è spenta e non risponde nessuno: ____ tutti.' (uscire, azione probabile nel passato)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": true,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 0.5,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.usage.probability",
        "label": "futuro anteriore for a past guess (saranno usciti)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "saranno usciti",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "sono usciti"
        ]
      },
      {
        "order_index": 1,
        "credit": 0.5,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.formation.future_anteriore",
        "label": "futuro anteriore formation, essere + agreement (saranno usciti)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "saranno usciti",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "avranno usciti",
          "saranno uscito"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "uscire",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "uscire - to go out / to leave",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.uscire.verb.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'They must have all gone out': La luce e spenta e non risponde nessuno: saranno usciti tutti. The futuro anteriore guesses about a completed past: 'saranno usciti' means 'they've probably gone out'. Uscire is a motion verb, so the auxiliary is essere and the participle agrees (usciti, masculine plural for 'tutti'). The passato prossimo 'sono usciti' would state it as fact; the compound future marks the inference.",
    "examiner_note": "Two markpoints per Rev 27: probability usage + futuro anteriore formation (with essere agreement), 0.5 each. Suppressed. 'sono usciti' is the wrong-tense catch; 'avranno usciti' (wrong auxiliary) and 'saranno uscito' (no agreement) are the formation catches.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "fu_cmd_01",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "verb_form.future",
    "subtopic": "usage.command_promise",
    "difficulty": 4,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Completa: 'Ti prometto che ____ alla tua festa, senza dubbio.' (venire, io)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": true,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.usage.command_promise",
        "label": "future in a promise (verrò)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "verrò",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "vengo",
          "verò"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "venire",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "venire - to come",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.venire.verb.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'I promise I'll come to your party': Ti prometto che verrò alla tua festa. A promise looks forward to an action you commit to, and Italian states that commitment in the future: 'prometto che verrò'. Using the present 'prometto che vengo' is possible in very casual speech but the future is the standard, firmer promise. (Verrò is the double-r future stem of venire.)",
    "examiner_note": "Visible: the promise frame makes the future natural, so the breadcrumb 'future in a promise' restates the context rather than leaking. 'vengo' is the present alternative; 'verò' the single-r formation slip.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "fu_cmd_02",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "verb_form.future",
    "subtopic": "usage.command_promise",
    "difficulty": 4,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Completa nel registro solenne dei comandamenti: 'Non ____.' (uccidere, tu)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": true,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.usage.command_promise",
        "label": "legalistic future as command (ucciderai)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "ucciderai",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "uccidere",
          "uccidi"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "uccidere",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "uccidere - to kill",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.uccidere.verb.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Thou shalt not kill': Non ucciderai. In solemn, legalistic or biblical language Italian gives a command in the future rather than the imperative: 'non ucciderai' is the fifth commandment, more absolute than the ordinary negative imperative 'non uccidere'. The register cue ('dei comandamenti') tells you the emphatic future, not the imperative, is wanted.",
    "examiner_note": "Register stated in the prompt (criterion 11). 'non uccidere' (negative tu imperative) and 'uccidi' are the ordinary-command alternatives the emphatic future displaces here.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "fu_cmd_03",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "verb_form.future",
    "subtopic": "usage.command_promise",
    "difficulty": 4,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Completa il rimprovero enfatico di un genitore: 'Adesso basta giocare: ____ i compiti e poi andrai a letto!' (fare, tu)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": true,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "verb_form.future.usage.command_promise",
        "label": "emphatic future as command (farai)",
        "any_phrases": [
          {
            "phrase": "farai",
            "match_at": "word"
          }
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "fai",
          "ferai"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "fare",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "fare - to do / to make",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.fare.verb.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Now you'll do your homework and then go to bed!': Farai i compiti e poi andrai a letto. An insistent order can be given in the future instead of the imperative, which makes it sound more like a non-negotiable decree: 'farai i compiti' is firmer than the plain 'fai i compiti'. The parallel 'andrai a letto' in the sentence sets the emphatic-future tone.",
    "examiner_note": "Visible; the emphatic register is cued and the sibling 'andrai' models it. 'fai' is the plain imperative; 'ferai' the wrong-stem formation slip (fare keeps far-).",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "fu_cmd_04",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "verb_form.future",
    "subtopic": "usage.command_promise",
    "difficulty": 4,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Completa la promessa: 'Ti giuro che non lo ____ mai più.' (fare, io)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": true,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
