        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "fare - to do / to make",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.fare.verb.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'I swear I'll never do it again': Ti giuro che non lo farò mai più. A solemn promise ('ti giuro') looks to the future: 'non lo farò mai più'. The present 'non lo faccio' would describe a current habit, not a commitment about what is to come; the promise needs the future.",
    "examiner_note": "Visible. 'faccio' is the present; 'ferò' the wrong-stem slip.",
    "version": 1
  },
