    "explanation": "'We'll wait here until the storm is over': Aspetteremo qui finche non finira il temporale. After 'finche (non)' pointing at a future endpoint, Italian uses the future: 'finche non finira'. English uses the present ('until it ends'), which is the pattern to resist. The 'non' after finche is expletive and does not make the sentence negative.",
